# Analytics_And_Telemetry

## 1. Applies when
Games with live operations, monetization, player progression tracking, or data-driven iteration.

## 2. This document owns
Analytics strategy, key metrics, and data collection design; telemetry event schema and instrumentation specifications; player behavior tracking: retention, engagement, progression, churn; monetization analytics: conversion, ARPU, LTV, purchase funnels; A/B testing framework and experiment design; data pipeline, storage, and visualization tooling; privacy compliance: GDPR, CCPA, COPPA, data retention policies.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Game design decisions driven by data (→ respective design docs); monetization design and pricing (→ Monetization_Design or Resource_And_Economy); server infrastructure and data storage implementation (→ Technical_Design); live operations event scheduling (→ LiveOps_Design).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Analytics Strategy & Key Metrics · 2. Telemetry Event Schema · 3. Player Behavior Tracking · 4. Monetization Analytics · 5. A/B Testing Framework · 6. Data Pipeline & Visualization · 7. Privacy & Compliance

## 5. Common boundaries
- Analytics owns "what to measure"; Gameplay_Systems owns "what the mechanic is".
- Telemetry events reference game systems but don't redefine them.
- Privacy compliance lives here; legal review may produce separate documentation.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check that telemetry events reference game systems from Gameplay_Systems.
- Check that retention metrics reference progression from Progression_Design.
- Check that privacy compliance references platform-specific requirements.
